      "span_text": "This is demonstrated by the large electron density around Cu 2+ (HOMO) and the distribution of electron density over the ligands in LUMO, while Cu 2+ is surrounded by hardly any charge density. The energy change (HOMO − LUMO) was lowered to ~0.23 eV. This low energy magnitude complies with the experimental observation of the preference of staphylopine toward copper [CITATION_2] ."
